{"id":14881289,"mediaExerciseId":"fd187df4-2084-47b7-82a1-22da71ef93ff","exerciseName":"4","chapterName":"11","chapterTitle":"Project Analysis and Evaluation","groupId":612351,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":375,"solutions":[{"id":6058835,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"Generally, a no-layoff policy will maintain the fixed costs of a company. This means that the degree of operating leverage relies on the cashflow. \n\nIf a company goes into a recession, then the DOL will be high. Remember that a high DOL means higher forecasting risk. This high forecasting risk may affect future investors since they will be doubtful of the profitability of the company. Thus, they need to liquidate some of their assets in order for them to increase the cash flow.\n\nOn the other hand, a company that is steadily improving can continue maximizing their profits since they no longer have to deal with payments included in laying off employees. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"945d39e1-b9d8-4b7e-8e98-31436072ff62","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":1}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":1488